<sec id="id-80160f7b-29ce-4355-c2c1-3ed5027c8ddd"><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="07dbe582-56a4-4cc1-ceab-2b181bcaefff" timestamp="1656534022174"?>Related actions and expectations<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="07dbe582-56a4-4cc1-ceab-2b181bcaefff"?></bold></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="7eb6cf5a-adf0-4ba8-ff38-56716c8eff49" timestamp="1656534016108"?>The organization should:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7eb6cf5a-adf0-4ba8-ff38-56716c8eff49"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="5baed836-8aea-43a3-e397-da43073e764b" timestamp="1656534016108"?>—    <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5baed836-8aea-43a3-e397-da43073e764b"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="cb3c9695-cab9-471f-ebde-df56c7a2028d" text="alternately use gender-inclusive language, non-sexist (generic) language and gender-neutral language (in which words do not vary according to gender) and gendered articles to address its internal and external stakeholders in an inclusive manner;" timestamp="1666858623077"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="a9445555-9295-488b-d37f-b6c81c3b69ca" timestamp="1670341297432"?>alternately use gender-inclusive language, non-sexist (generic) language and gender-neutral terms (for which words do not vary according to gender) and gendered articles specifically in all kind of internal and external communications related to promotion, hiring and research of work positions equally opened for women and men ;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a9445555-9295-488b-d37f-b6c81c3b69ca"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="7a8c38b2-b47f-4808-cff1-0bf12af5c07d" timestamp="1656534016108"?>—    prefer the use of lists of persons in alphabetical order rather than hierarchical order, and present the person’s complete identity (first name, name, job position, etc.);<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7a8c38b2-b47f-4808-cff1-0bf12af5c07d"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="09183909-92a1-4fd4-ef80-0abbfa13bc8e" timestamp="1656534016108"?>—    <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="09183909-92a1-4fd4-ef80-0abbfa13bc8e"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="3c918b8d-0c61-4136-d861-6449cdd9caf0" text="guarantee gender equality and" timestamp="1669026572323"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="5fb724b2-0e55-4440-bee2-76ff7f6ac623" timestamp="1669026572323"?>ensure gender parity in communication and gender balance representation among speakers<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5fb724b2-0e55-4440-bee2-76ff7f6ac623"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="319e1be8-f206-49cf-b7be-aa5e27a68d37" timestamp="1656534016108"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="319e1be8-f206-49cf-b7be-aa5e27a68d37"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="856aee8e-1052-43ab-aceb-d865c7da1083" text="parity in its communications materials and parity between speakers" timestamp="1669026572323"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="5d57a2b2-9f58-4a73-b9af-1c5be4197f5b" timestamp="1656534016108"?>;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5d57a2b2-9f58-4a73-b9af-1c5be4197f5b"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="f11e73b7-65d2-4ce3-dcf6-f83c0fc608a6" timestamp="1656534016108"?>—    use images that respect and promote gender equality;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f11e73b7-65d2-4ce3-dcf6-f83c0fc608a6"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="9e884a8a-901b-47a8-e37d-ff9dae8cd604" timestamp="1656534016108"?>—    allow equal speaking times or, when this is not possible, guarantee<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="9e884a8a-901b-47a8-e37d-ff9dae8cd604"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="f0cb4768-7f4b-4324-b166-9dedbd26595b" text=" gender-based participation that is representative of the personnel;" timestamp="1674733382958"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="2483416d-0c95-4c47-d443-7007fc3c62b4" timestamp="1674733387112"?> gender-balanced participation<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2483416d-0c95-4c47-d443-7007fc3c62b4"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="0f20bf40-fe10-43ab-9aa2-bad6874ea366" timestamp="1656534016108"?>—    <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="0f20bf40-fe10-43ab-9aa2-bad6874ea366"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="de4553b3-82a4-437b-ad86-5b1c9e8ad760" text="promote feminine and masculine models on an equal footing in all its forms of communication." timestamp="1669026904849"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="413ab809-1a65-4914-e73a-3fb91c672591" timestamp="1669026906431"?>promote role models that go beyond gender stereotypes and expand traditional roles assigned to women and men in all its forms of communication.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="413ab809-1a65-4914-e73a-3fb91c672591"?></p></sec>